response.Q0: At first, I was just clicking randomly which was costing me money. Then I realised that the further out the nodes, the higher the number but greater the cost of using the node detector. I realised it made sense for me to just click the outer nodes and find a green number as high as possible, then move the spider in that direction.
response.Q1: As above, it made sense to me to just select the outer node and go for one that was at least green/positive and above 30.
response.Q2: It took me a while to realise the structure of the web, that the value of the nodes increase as it went further out from the middle, and that the cost of the node inspector also increased. It was hard waiting to use the node inspector after clicking on the outer nodes as I just wanted to click another one but had to wait.
